namedLocations.description: Gujarat (/ˌɡʊdʒəˈrɑːt/, Gujarati: [ˈɡudʒəɾɑt] ) is a state on the western coast of India with a coastline of 1,600 km (990 mi) – most of which lies on the Kathiawar peninsula – and a population in excess of 60 million. It is the sixth largest Indian state by area and the ninth largest state by population. Gujarat is bordered by Rajasthan to the northeast, Daman and Diu to the south, Dadra and Nagar Haveli and Maharashtra to the southeast, Madhya Pradesh to the east, and the Arabian Sea and the Pakistani province of Sindh to the west. Its capital city is Gandhinagar, while its largest city is Ahmedabad. The Gujarati-speaking people of India are indigenous to the state. The economy of Gujarat is the fifth-largest state economy in India with ₹14.96 lakh crore (US$220 billion) in gross domestic product and a per capita GDP of ₹157,000 (US$2,300). Gujarat ranks fifteenth among Indian states in human development index.

transcript.text: Hello welcome to on print shop.
This video is about setup code form fields.
In this video we will see what are the code form fields and how to create it for existing product and custom product.
So what are the code form fields?
If you go to the front store and click on request a quote.
So here a customer can fill this quote form and ask you for the quotation.
So we term this quote form.
These fields are the quote form fields.
So if you see there are two kind of product type 1 is existing products.
Existing product means the product which are available for sale on your website and which are listed.
Custom product is the one which is not listed on your website and it is a completely customizable product.
So customer has to fill this form.
So we can create the these form fields let's say website size lamination if you select the existing 1.
So for existing one if for example if you select any of the product let's say T-shirt and half slips.
So what are the form fields are coming over here.
So depending on the situation we can create the form fields basis on the specific product, basis on the existing product and basis on the custom products.
So how can we create these form fields for that just go to the admin site, go to store configuration here is manage form fields.
So once you click on add button you can create a form field just click on add button.
So here it is for which store you are creating this form field just select this two title the form field title.
Just suppose we want to create a form field for turn around time then the description if you want to give some information then form field type.
So here we are giving three kind of form fields one is for code 1 is for higher designer and the third one is for the templates.
So we have to select codes here.
Then product specific attribute it is for all product or for a specific product if it's a specific product.
So you have to select specific product for which specific product.
So under the specific product you can see the custom code product one of the as a product.
That means it is for custom products.
So right now we are creating the form field for a custom product.
Same way you can create it for all products or as well As for specific product by just selecting the data from here.
Then display description in pop up activate it or not.
Then sorting order at which place you want to keep it.
For example, we are keeping it at let's say point #10 then as we have created it as a turn around time, so we can give it a text box.
It may be a radio button.
So depending on your requirement, you can select.
Right now we are taking it as a text box.
Then the validation allow none means customer can leave it blank.
If you will click on require.
So it is mandatory field.
Customer has to fill it.
So right now we are taking it as a required field and we are just saving it.
So in that way, we can easily create a custom code field.
So if you go at front end and if we refresh this page, repeat here, we can see the turn around time which we have created right now.
If you have any queries and concerns regarding this video, please connect with us at support onprintshop.com.
Thank you.
